##replace NA string with actual empty Nan for all columns
GDP['IMF (2026)[6]'] = GDP['IMF (2026)[6]'].replace('N/a', np.nan)
GDP['World Bank (2024)[7]'] = GDP['World Bank (2024)[7]'].replace('N/a', np.nan)
GDP['United Nations (2024)[8]'] = GDP['United Nations (2024)[8]'].replace('N/a', np.nan)

# remove first world row
GDP = GDP.drop(GDP.index[0])

## Create new column that has IMF data and fills missing IMF's with data from the UN and Worldbank in that prioritization order
GDP['IMF'] = GDP['IMF (2026)[6]'].combine_first(GDP['United Nations (2024)[8]']).combine_first(GDP['World Bank (2024)[7]'])

## print the rows missing IMF again to ensure new IMF column is filled correctly

## load in the hierarchy information
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bcaffo/MRIcloudT1volumetrics/master/inst/extdata/multilevel_lookup_table.txt"
multilevel_lookup = pd.read_csv(url, sep = "\t").drop(['Level5'], axis = 1)
multilevel_lookup = multilevel_lookup.rename(columns = {
    "modify"   : "roi",
    "modify.1" : "level4",
    "modify.2" : "level3",
    "modify.3" : "level2",
    "modify.4" : "level1"})
multilevel_lookup = multilevel_lookup[['roi', 'level4', 'level3', 'level2', 'level1']]

## Now load in the subject data
id = 127
subjectData = pd.read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/smart-stats/ds4bio_book/main/book/assetts/kirby21AllLevels.csv")
subjectData = subjectData.loc[(subjectData.type == 1) & (subjectData.level == 5) & (subjectData.id == id)]
subjectData = subjectData[['roi', 'volume']]
## Merge the subject data with the multilevel data
subjectData = pd.merge(subjectData, multilevel_lookup, on = "roi")
subjectData = subjectData.assign(icv = "ICV")
subjectData = subjectData.assign(comp = subjectData.volume / np.sum(subjectData.volume))

In[19]:
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import pandas as pd

path = ['icv', 'level1', 'level2', 'level3', 'level4', 'roi']
value_col = 'comp'

labels = pd.unique(subjectData[path].values.ravel()).tolist()

sources = []
targets = []
values = []

for i in range(len(path) - 1):
    temp_df = subjectData.groupby([path[i], path[i+1]])[value_col].sum().reset_index()
    sources.extend(temp_df[path[i]].map(lambda x: labels.index(x)))
    targets.extend(temp_df[path[i+1]].map(lambda x: labels.index(x)))
    values.extend(temp_df[value_col])

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Sankey(
    node = dict(
      pad = 15,
      thickness = 20,
      label = labels
    ),
    link = dict(
      source = sources,
      target = targets,
      value = values
    ))])

fig.update_layout(title_text="Sankey html", font_size=10)
fig.show()
fig.write_html("sankey.html", include_plotlyjs='cdn', full_html=True)
